\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 He didn't have any casual work or part time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh no. No, no, he was - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Do you ever remember him being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. He was never out of work. No. That was at High Park Colliery, just over here you know, it's closed now. High Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You can see those cottages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. That's right. Yes, where he - 
well the family lived there once. And they used to call it slaughter pit because there were always men getting killed. Mind you that's years ago. But that's true. Yes, it had a bad record. 'Cos my grandmother Soar, you know, there were no ambulances place
s and there were nothing then, she hoped when they used to bring them out of pit, either dead or alive, she - did what she could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Those cottages were right next to the pit weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. It were them cottages were here. Cottages are still the
re now you know. The pits not though of course. Don't know whether the shafts are there are not I'm sure. No. There were two shafts. There's generally two you know at these pits. One for the air to go down, one for the air to come up. High cast and - one 
own cast and one's up cast. That's what they call it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Out of Bedfordshire. She was born at Clifton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Do you know whether she had any jobs before she was married to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, well - well she w
as apprenticed for a schoolteacher. Yes. And I can tell you her wages - half a crown a week. And they were starved to death. And Mrs Witham, my mother's sister, she was the same. And she got a place at Hamble - in - in the Lake District somewhere in't it,
 Ambleside, up there. Well she went there to better herself a bit. Then she came back and settled here and got married you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your mother work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 She wouldn't have any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Because grandmother Bygrave died and she sort of - kept the house on 'cos Grandad Bygrave lived with us you see 'til he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Which house did you lived in the longest, you lived in Hilltop and then you moved just down the road here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well I think they're about s
imilar. Oh - oh wait a minute. Oh no, I shall live down here longer. Because I was - I was about - Don was - Don was - let's see - six - I should be about - oh I was nearly ten when Don was born. Listen, there was only - he was born on the 21st of March a
nd I was born on the 24th. And if he'd been three days later there would have been ten years. But of course that little sister was between us. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How many rooms were there in that house in Nottingham Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well there was three down and three up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Downstairs you would regard two of them as reception rooms would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. And a kitchen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sister live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, we had - we used to have - ministers live with us - occasionally. Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 As a lodger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Used to have a woman that - she was rather crippled in the back and she couldn't - work anywhere else if you understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 But she didn't live in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 She just came daily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What sort of duties did she do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Cleaning, help in general way you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How many hours a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh well, they was - they didn't bother then, no, perhaps 'til dinner time, nine 'til twelve or - something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How did you get on with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 All right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What did she call you and hour mother, did she call you by your Christian names?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well she did me. Oh no, she called mother with her - proper name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Mrs Soar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Soar. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What did you call her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well I used to call her Sarah. Her name was Sarah.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. It was always done - had to do in those days. Now my grandad he was a builder you know, gra
ndad Bygrave, and in the little kitchen he - he built a sink and then he built a copper outside and we wat the only one about in Hilltop as had a copper then. You know, you lit the fire underneath, you know what I mean? 'Cos we'd coal you know, me dad had
 
coal same as I. Yes. Yes, and I'll tell you there was one tap there for six houses. If it got frozen everybody had to come out with - they'd boil their kettle and - put a cloth in and get it red hot and keep dabbing it all on the pipes 'til it thawed. 'Co
s you couldn't get no water with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Do you ever remember your mother or your father mending or making family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well they used to - they used to - not making I can't, but they used to patch and mend, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Would your mother do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were most of your clothes new in those days or did you have some secondhand?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh no, no, always new. Yes, because a lot - lot of people did make a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Where were they bought from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well we used to buy the material. There used to be Pa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 's come round then. You know what a Pa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
 is? The man that sells things from door to door. You'd perhaps pay sixpence a week and they'd let you have your stuff and you'd perhaps pay - what you could. Oh I can't pay nothing this week, we haven't got any you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 He was called a Pa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, a Pa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 cky}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 . Packman really. But they used to call them Pa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 's - nickname you see. Yes. Packman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 He was like a credit club salesman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, that's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What about shoes, did your father ever repair any boots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No, never. Mind there was cobblers in Hilltop. Used to call them cobblers you know, not boot repairers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your father help your mother with any of the work in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't think he did. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did he ever do the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Oh yes, he always did used to see to the fires. Now you know what they used - all round in district is the rake at night, put a raker on. Do you know what that is? You do don't you? Well it's a big lump of coal - no,
 you put a big lump on, half as big as that, then you put slack behind it. And then you go to bed of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 It keeps it in all night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. And you just knock it up in the morning and then you've got a good fire you see. Now I had a - my mother'
s brother lived at Welling in Hertfordshire - he was on the Great Northern and they used to come down here for a holiday. Well you know, they were frightened to death. My dad says, I'll be raking. They'd think the blessed house were going to be burnt down
. They did. Yes. And then you know we couldn't understand what they said very well. She used to say, what does he sound like. You see. They couldn't understand me dad you know. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your father do any decorating in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. We - wel
l women used to do it then. Neighbours, you know, they'd come and they'd - they'd do your room for paper it and - there were no paper tops then, it was all whitewash. Whitewash the ceiling and do the - perhaps do it for half a crown. And then you give the
m a good dinner in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What about repairs to the house or improvements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Oh well, the landlord - did that, I can remember - in our front room up there, at Hilltop, they want - red quarries. And I can remember 'em - all the row, six houses, they took
 them out and got the dirt out and - put boarded floors in, I can remember that ever so well. 'Cos we had a plant, I stayed - you had to go through the front room upstairs you see. And we had a plank to walk on while they did it, I remember that. I was on
ly about - oh I should be about five then I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 When your were a small boy did your father ever help to dress you or undress you or bath you or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't think he did. No. Can't remember as he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Can you ever remember him reading to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
No. Me mother did that you know, being a schoolteacher. I knew - I knew - I could write me name and do everything when I went to school, I was five when I started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your father ever tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, he used to tell a lot of tales, you know, and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did he ever take you out without your Mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Yes. Yes. Often. We once went to a flower show at Riddings, you've heard of talk of Riddings haven't you, it's over here. Yes, Riddings. It's 
before you get to Alfreton. On the main road, the main bus road. Oh there used to be two mills at Riddings you know. Yes, they've not been pulled down that long. 'Cos me dad used to say to me, now there's a puzzle here, he used to say, the Riddings Mill s
tands on you hill, spell it with two letters. I.T. you see, Yes. And of course I couldn't - get it 'til -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What kind of mills were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 I don't know what mills they were I'm sure, but believe they were corn mills. Oh you could see 'em for miles. Now we lived on }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 Hilton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
 you could see Crouch Stand. That's - you know what I mean - that's for the South Noss in't it. Well you see it's all built now, you can't see it. We could see the lights flashing. Now that's - hasn't been there long that stand you kn
ow. You know, the quarries and that had to move it back for safety. This is quite modern one, new, this one that's here now. Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 There's a tale about the light isn't there, it's supposed to flash for some reason, purpose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well it's - it's in memory of the South Notts isn't it. Something else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 I thought it's supposed to flash so many times a day and the number of times it flashes is related to the number of men who died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, very likely. I've not heard that. No, I've not heard that. Yes, I've no doubt, I shouldn't be surprised.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 When you were a ld did you have any jobs to do around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes. I did. Scrubbing floors and - I used to go and scrub floors for neighbours. Perhaps - give me tuppence. And do
 you know, I used to save that. 'Til I got enough money to take me to Nottingham. And I used to go up, you know, New }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 Thorpe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
 station. There was nothing on roads }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 then}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
. It's either Newthorpe or Kimberley station you had to go to. I forget how much it was, I know I used to go by myself. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 For how long did you used to do these little jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh - 'til I wasn't - 'til I got a job. When I left school at fourteen I think. I was out - I was messing about a month or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You didn't carry on with these jobs after you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
No, didn't. 'Cos it were all bed and work then. Eleven hours a day. Six 'til five. And six - yes, and six 'til twelve on Saturday, and no holidays then. There were no holidays - only Bank Holidays. You got Bank Holiday
 but that's all. Well holidays weren't thought of. They weren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Your two brothers were much younger than you weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh I've lost both them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well Donald, Don, he was a clerk in Nottingham. Prior - a timber and
 slate merchants on Canal Street, but - the firm went wrong, they spent too much money you know, the bosses drinking and, you know, having a good time. And he - then he got another job and - he died three years ago, he was only sixty. See, how old was he?
 Don. Ten years younger than me. Aye, seventy - aye, he was sixty - sixty-one when he died.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did they ever do any jobs around the house the same as you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, not much. No, they didn't do anything much, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You being the eldest, did you help the younger children with things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes. Take 'em out in the carriages and - all such as that you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How about helping them to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well we just showed them at the table to use the - knives and forks and things like that of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 And you'd take them out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes. Used to take 'em out. Out in the carriage as we called them, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 
mail carts}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  then you know. Prambacots - not perambulator, prambacots they used to call them. Prambacots. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time when you were a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, went to bed early. Every night, had to do then. Especially in summer time - I mean wintertime. Yes. Oh you had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Who put you to bed when you were very small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh me mother used to go
 upstairs with me 'cos I were very nervous. Candles then you know. And do you know, that house where we first lived at, we had a lamp on table you know, just one burner - paraffin lamp. Everybody were the same. Used to fetch a pint of paraffin, that was -
 penny then. Used to last about a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Can you remember about what age you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh I did when we came down here. Be about ten I should think. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you share the bedroom with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. My grandfather. I used to call him father and me dad dad. Yes. 'Cos you see I was tend to - like nearly ten before anymore came }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 along}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  - well you see losing that sister I - I couldn't just remember her but - see I was by myself until ten. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How long was your grandfather with you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh 'til he died. He died - down here. Don was born in March and he died in November. That was 1906.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 In the same year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 And he was seventy - he was sixty-nine, grandad Bygrave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What were the sleeping arrangements for the whole of the family then, there'd be you and your grandad in one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 And your mother and father in another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 In the other. And then we had a spare bedroom. Oh when I got bigger I went in this bedroom, left me grandad you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 When your other brothers came along there was plenty of room for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, they were both born down here you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 At the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 bigger}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Plenty of room then. They were big bedrooms, not like they make 'em today. Mind you there wa
sn't wardrobes and things fitted in like there is today, no. No. No. And yes, I'll tell you what there's never been no - baths in them you know. Oh no, there'd be not baths in - practically all these houses down here there was no baths in them. But they'v
e had them put in since. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 So where did you have a bath in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 There. I've got our big bath now. A big }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 sync}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  bath. Yes, you have it on fire, sort of on the hearth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You have it in front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Yes, that's right. The
n - clean it out and hang it up outside, outside back door they used to hang 'em, a big - they had a big stake put in you know, iron rectangle. Used to have a boiler you know, you know side boilers don't you. Used to get plenty of water and - kettles boil
ing and big pan on th'hob at side of fire. How you got your hot water. And women you know, they - washed your backs - I mean, a miner, his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 wife\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 wash}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
 his back - when he got in bath or else as children grew up they'd do it you see. Oh that was a regular thing. Yes. And if your - if you - if it was hot weather you'd save all your water, you'd soak something - go and water your plants in garden. Yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Before you'd left school can you remember how often you had a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well every week. Yes. Saturday night used to be - Friday or Saturday night used to be bath night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was it the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 practice}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  to change your clothes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Yes. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Where did your family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh we had it in the kitchen - where it were cooked. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were there any times when you had it in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 Always}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, always in the kitchen where it were cooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What did she cook on, was it a range or a gas stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Yes, a range, coal. Oh coal, there were no gas then, only gas rings. Gas - I can remember gas stoves coming in - well you see everybody'd got plenty of coal here. In mining district you see. There were nothing else. I know when l
ads used to go to pit their mothers used to be nearly dead that first day. Thinking they'd get killed, their not being used to it, can you see. I've known women to go with them first day, yes, mothers, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 When was breakfast eaten, at what time in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh I used to get up early with me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 granddad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 , I did. I used to get up at half past five. And have it with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Because he liked to get up early?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh he always did, yes. I've known my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 granddad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  to walk from here to Baysford gas
 works and do a days work and come back. They had to do, it were all of that, there were no benefits then, there weren't a penny from nowhere, you know that. Well he lived 'til he was sixty-nine, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 granddad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  Bygrave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You'd have breakfast with your grandfather then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What about your father, would he have gone out earlier than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, he'd - he'd be about the same time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Can you remember what you used to have to eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh used to have bacon. We didn't h
ave a lot of eggs. Bacon and also we had a lot of fried bread I can remember and I used to like fried bread. You know, put it in the frying pan with some good dripping and - you know, and then fry it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was it normal to have tea with your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes. Plenty of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you have anything different for breakfast on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't think so. I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What about midday meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well we used to have - oh yes, good dinners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 In the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Now I'll tell you
 what we did. This were a Bedfordshire custom, we always used to have the pudding first, the sweet first. Aye, that's it. Yes. Aye, I know that. Me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 granddad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  he wouldn't have it no different. Mind you I don't know do that here now not myself, but we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was Sunday dinner time any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 About twelve I should think. No, no different. Used to have it at twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was the actual food any different on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. We - we used to have - half a shoulder of mutton for donkey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 \rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  years. And I used to fetch it sometimes from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 Sanderson\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
 - you don't know }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 Sanderson\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
 butchers shop. Well you know on Dovecote Lane, just past the school, there's their shop there, a little building, have you noticed it. You come down Millthorpe on the other side. Well that was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 Sanderson\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
 butchers. And it used to be about two and - two and seven or two and eight or two and nine, half a shoulder of mutton. And it used to last us 'til Thursday. Me mam used to do it up in different ways. Can you see? And we used to go t
here - I used to go and take the bill. Not every week. We always used to have an orange at Christmas and we thought we'd got thousand pounds.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What about an evening meal, you'd have a sort of a tea would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 We had tea and then we had a little 
supper. Had a lot of Quaker Oats then you know. 'Cos milk was - how much was it - threeha'pence a pint I think - if I remember right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Oh yes. And I sometimes bake a bit here. I get bowl on flo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 u}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 r and knead it well on me knees, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did she make any jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Yes. She used to make enough jam to last the winter. And we'd a little spare bedroom up there. And - do you know what it was stuck down with newspaper then. Used to make some paste with flour and water and do up the jam, and we'd a brass }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 pan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 . It were about - like that. Oh I forget how much it held. Yes, she used to make enough to last us - through the winter. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What about bottled fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. Nothing like that. Very seldom
 was we had a tin of fruit. I don't remember us having much tinned fruit. It was a luxury then you know, there wasn't much tinned fruit about. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did she ever make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What about wine, homemade wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, haven't got no wines, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't remember her making medicines, no. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was there any beer brewed in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your mother or father grow their own vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, we had 
to. Now that house up there I tell you was two and nine a week and there was a common garden with - with those houses. Every house had a common garden. And we'd a big one at the front and a big one at the back as well. You had to do then, my word. You had
 to do to live.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You didn't very often see tinned fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
No. No, never saw tinned fruit. Might have had a tin of salmon occasionally, of course that was cheaper then you know and more common. And oh I'll tell you we used to have sardines, there we
re a lot of sardines about then. And they'd make their own cake you know. I know our neighbours, she used to make hers at Sunday while she'd got the - not cooking dinner and then put it on yard to cool for tea. Cake. I can see it there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you keep any hens or pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 We used to have a few animals, we didn't have any pigs, not to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Who looked after the hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh we used to look after 'em between us. Take scraps to 'em and all you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Can you remember how many times a week you'd have meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well should have it most days. Aye, we always had meat, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Can you remember tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I can't remember any tinned - there used to be corned beef - but not in tins. That was about first I can remember.
 As we called corned beef and - I believe it was tuppence a quarter then. Now I'll tell you, I used to go to stores up top of the hill here, I used to fetch a quarter of butter and half an ounce of thick twist for me dad, it were fivepence. Best Danish bu
tter then was one and two a pound. And thick twist was sevenpence an ounce. Now what is it now, about five bob. Five or six shillings. I don't know. Mind you I've have a few Woodbines but I don't smoke a pipe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Can you remember there being any extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 I can tell you one - now, me dad - his eldest brother was engine- wright at Granville Collieries, that's near \endash 
 in - yes, in Derbyshire. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 In Derbyshire mining district. Well he used to often send grandmother Soar a har
e. And - she didn't want it all and she always used to send us some. That's all I can remember - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How often would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well - in holiday times. I can't remember us - having anything - special like that. No. Mind you sometimes we used to 
have a - kill a fowl and - cook it and have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you ever remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No. No. No, was never like that because you see - a deputy was a good position in them days you know - those days rather. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your father have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
No. No, he didn't, no, we'd always plenty. Well I'll tell you what, we used to go to Skegness every year for a week, me and mam. And used to take this servant girl with us, 'cos she'd no mon
ey. Well there wasn't many families could do that you couldn't go for a day let alone a week. That was when I was a youngster before Don came along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 When you were seated at the table were you allowed to talk during a meal or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes. I mean we weren't brought up strict like that. Of course we had to behave you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 But you could talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh we could talk, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 When you wanted something from the table could you ask for it to be passed down to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, it could be passed, yes. Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you have to eat everything that was put in front of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, no, I don't think so, if I didn't like a thing - have something else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 If you left something uneaten on the plate did your mother complain?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't think so. No. Because there were things I didn't like, I didn't like hard cheese for a start. Never have done. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What about if you wanted a second helping, could you ask for one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, you could ask for a second helping, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, I had to hold that properly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 And sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were you allowed to bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Not - not - not whe
n the meal was there. We did after, you could play on the table. We used to play underneath, we used to drape it with clothes and - get underneath you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 This was after the meal was over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh Yes. We did that - I can remember doing that up here. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 When could you leave the table after the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well when it was finished, we - well we should all get up together if you can understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you all sit down at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you have your own special place at table or did you sit anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well I think we did, yes. In special place, your own place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How was the meal served, who would serve the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 My mother served it. Used to call mam you know, not mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What order were you served in, any special way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't - remember.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Where would your younger brothers sit and have their food before they could sit up at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well we used to have a high chair for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Who would feed them, your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Well I think we all give 'em a bit if, you know, we - pleased - you know for them to be there if you understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 About what age would they be able to join in at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well as soon as they could sit up, before they could walk you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 As soon as they could sit on a chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Yes. Not an ordinary chair you see, they'd fall off wouldn't they. These high chairs you know they'd - they'd a board at the front and the arms at the side hadn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 The women who used to come and help your mother, did she ever have any meals in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh she had 'em with us. Oh yes. She treated her as one of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 There was no difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was your mother an easy person for you to talk to?
