Well - now you see I was ten when Don were born of course, I were getting - when he were knocking about - oh I used to take him out in his carriage you know. Yes. The young one - well - I was nineteen when he was born. Basil. Yes. Nineteen. See he wa
s - was I nineteen. Yes, I was. Yes. And he got killed in the last war and he was ever so clever. Oh he was - aye, too clever. He was a tank inspector. And it turned over at Lincoln, on one of the slopes, they were trying it out, cut both his legs off. An
d
 he'd just got to - he left a baby daughter. Nine months old. And this is her, look. She married officer in the Navy. Of course her mother married again you know, of course. But he's been - oh very good to her. Like a second father you know. He was very g
ood - he hadn't any and - of course they've had another since that. Another little boy. So that's the only relation I've got alive beside cousins if you understand.
