\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh they all went then, they did in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 All your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Ladies everything black and - men and all, if you hadn't got a black suit you had to borrow one from somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 So they all wore black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Always, yes, deep black. Yes, they'd wear deep black for a year. Yes, a year. Used to be it then. And I know poor people in Hilltop if anyone died they'd come round collecting for them, you see, to bury them. Yee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were you taken out visiting neighbours friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Who would take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did she ever take you out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't remember going - me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 granddad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  used to take me to Nottingham. To Tommy }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 Lipton\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
. That was - and he used to buy me - there used to be fourpenny bars of chocolate then as big as that for fourpence. I used to take it home and put it on the pantry shelf. Keep nibbling at it 'til it had gone. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you go out often with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, quite a lot. I used to go to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3814368\charrsid3172719 Swadlingcote}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  for a weekend to see me dad's brother. Other places too. Used to go to Goose Fair. We went once me mother went with us. And
 he put on his shoulders here and he turned round to me mother and he says, where's our Bernard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You'd go to Swadlingcote quite often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, I used to go with dad, we used to go Saturday and come back Sunday. And we used to have to go to - Burton
-on-Trent then you know on the train. And then there were trams run from Burton-on-Trent to Swadlingcote - tramcars. Yes. Used to go on those. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Can you tell me about going to Skegness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh we used to go }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  a week and - I can't remember a lot
 about it but I was - well I was only a nipper then you know, but we went, yes, we'd go every year. Yes. Then we had day trips you know. We used to go to Skegness and - if we went to Cleethorpes we did well. And that used to be - two and nine return then 
f
or a grown up you know. Two and nine from Newthorpe station and we used to have a saloon, you know what a saloon carriage is? A long carriage and - no compartments, seats all round and tables down the centre. Yes. Oh we had some jolly times then. Oh and w
e used to - I'll tell you - we went to Matlock you know, we used to go to Matlock from here in horse brakes and it used to take us twelve hours. We used to start at eight in the morning and get back practically at eight at night. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10186699\charrsid3172719 And when we got to Ripley we had to get out of the - brake while it went down Hawkesley Hill, do you know Hawkesley Hill? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Going through Ripley into Derbyshire. Well we used to have to get out then and walk down 'cos it was too steep. And when we was coming back we used to get out an
d - perhaps help give the brake a shove up the hill, and if it was Saturday - which it was - we used to get to Ripley and stop in Ilkley Market for about an hour. And that used to be about one and six - the fare then. And we used to take our food with us 
o
n the - you know, we had to get up some steps to get on the seat with the driver, quite high up he was you know. Used to take a ham boiled and - cakes you know and pastries and everything you wanted and we'd a certain place we went to every year. And the 
e
lderly ladies, they'd stay behind and cook the food up. Them that couldn't walk very well you see, it was an outing for them and we used to - go round and we used to have a ride - there was a switchback there and it was tuppence to go on. Oh we did have a
 lovely time. That's in Matlock. Side of the Derwent. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 They've got a recreation place there now haven't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Oh that's - Matlock Bath in't it. Yes, well this is Matlock - where the fish pond is. Where we used to stay. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How did you spend Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well it was ordinary. Without we went to Nottingham Saturday afternoon. With our parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh I'd go to church Sunday. I went - they didn't - they didn't tell us to go, we knew. We knew what it was. W
e used to - I used to go three times every Sunday. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10186699\charrsid3172719 Sunday morning, afternoon Sunday school, and then I used to go in the evening. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you wear different clothes on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No, wh
ere we once had some snow and we were making a slide and a neighbour came out and - my word - she didn't half carry on. Because we were sliding on Sunday. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your parents think it was wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Definitely. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did they attend a place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. They did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What denomination was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Me dad, he was a chapel - a Methodist and he left Methodist and went into Eastwood church choir, he was in there about forty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 That was the Eastwood parish church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How often would they go, every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh mam played the organ I tell you for fifty years at Hilltop Mission church here. That started in my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10186699\charrsid3172719 granddad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  Bygraves' front parlour. That little mission church. Grandad Bygraves' front parlour. That was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10186699\charrsid3172719 cottage}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
 in Hilltop, it's still sanding. And then they - this - Mrs Alcocks joined - wood - wood place, joiners shop, and I don't know how they got it, anyway they got this place and turned it into a mission. Yes, that's how that
 - and we used to - we were living near it you know, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10186699\charrsid3172719 Granddad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
 Bygraves cleaned it. And we used to have all the communion vessels at our house. And when it was Holy Communion, me mam - she - there was no wafers like there is today you know - she used to get
 two slices of bread and cut the crust off and then cut it in little squares, you see. And we - kept the bottle of - the bottle of wine, I think that was kept at the church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 So your mother and father were both regular church attenders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10186699\charrsid3172719 Granddad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  Bygrave was, I used to go with him every Sunday morning to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10186699\charrsid3172719 Greasley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  church when I was a lad.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Greasley Parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, and we used to walk from Hilltop here you know. He wouldn't walk on the path, he said it was softer on the road to w
alk. Of course they weren't gas tarred then you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10186699\charrsid3172719 It was all just like - you know, slag and dirt in it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
And you know they used to brush when there'd been a bad storm - they had to sweep it you know and they used to brush all the mud into the gutters. And if you wanted to go across the road you had to jump over you see. 'Til it dried up again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You went to Sunday school aw well didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you go on any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I can't remember, not very - oh well 
- why there were grown ups as well, it wasn't just for the children if you understand. We used to go in brakes to - the reservoir. Wallgreen reservoir. Yes. And take our food there like a picnic you know. 'Course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Would this be organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. We wouldn't think of walking, it was too far in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were there any other activities that you took part in that were organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Used to be Band of Hope. That was a weekly meeting you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you belong to the choir?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, I was in the choir. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did the choir have any activities of its own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't think so, only just practicing for the church - you know, special occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was there anything else organised by the church that you were a member of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
No, I don't think so, no. You see, there weren't a lot of activities, you had to keep in your own district then. 'Cos you couldn't get anywhere, there were nothing to take you if you understand. I know once there was a confirmatio
n service at Kimberley church and - they hired a wagonette to take those that were being confirmed, you know, that sort of special occasion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't think grace was a lot. No. I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, had to say prayers, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you ever have family prayers all together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. I don't remember that. Mind they read the Bible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your father take an interest in politics do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Not a lot I don't think those days. He was a cricketer you know. Just local matches if you understand. A lot - the men did in those days 'cos there were nothing else to do, you had to make your own entertainment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 He wasn't interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. Don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 So you don't know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No I don't really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh - they were Conservatives. Mother was, yes. Grandpa Bygraves was and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Have you any idea why your mother held Conservative views?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, but I - she was bought up that way you see. That's it. You see, churchmen they were all Conservatives then weren't they. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Do you remember your father voting in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, he'd always vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 1919? Oh yes. Oh he used to vote, oh yes, I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You don't know what party he voted for do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 The Conservatives then. Yes. Vote Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 In some places at that time we're told that some men felt they were ri
sking losing their job or even their house if they voted differently from their employer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Yes. Yes, that's quite true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Do you know if your father ever felt himself under that kind of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No - I - I don't remember, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 He was never a member of a political party was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No. He was more - studying you know for his - to get his certificates. Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You can't remember him working for the party at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Nor your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Any other political activities at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Outside their work how did your parents spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well - mother spent most of her time churching or getting - you know there was a big choir there in those days a
nd - had a lot of practices, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 This would be your mother's main interest outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Oh it was, oh yes, it was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 And the organ and teaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, and teaching people, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Apart from that did she go anywhere for sheer enjoyment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
No. Don't think so. No, I used to hear 'em talk about pantomimes and things but I never went. Nottingham Empire you know, there was nothing nearer then, the Nottingham Empire. Some of the people used to go but - oh, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  thought if you were going to them places you were going to the devil. That's how I was brought up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What time did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh they - they were longer hours then you know. I should think about four. Four o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How many evenings a week would he spend at home? All of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, he never went out. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your father ever go to a club or pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You were telling me he was interested in cricket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did he actually play cricket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, he played cricket, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did he ever go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was he a betting man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs, like sick clubs or a funeral club or a book club.?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
No, only the doctor, I think that's all. Of course that was a regular thing, then, when I was younger. The doctor used to come every week and you'd pay so much a week off your bill you see. Yes. There was no one that paid - straight away if you understand
. The doctors' liked that, they'd a regular income. Of course things were different, you know, how it is now don't you. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How did you get on with your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, my brothers - oh all right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was there anyone that you felt particularly close to of the two of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't think so. Well we were close you know, we were all brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 I played with me cousin. Yes. Sister's - mother's sister's - daughter. She's in Walton Park now at
 Nottingham, she married a schoolmaster. He - he was this way and then he got a position in Nottingham. And he had to go and live in the city boundaries if you understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Where would you play mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 On the road. There were no traffic then. The
re was the mail cart and perhaps a brewery wagon or two you know. Brewery wagon or two. They were all - horses then you know. There used to be a man come selling balm from Kimberley in a barrow. Balm, to make your own beer you see. You know, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10186699\charrsid3172719 herb}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  beer, yes. You'd take a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10186699\charrsid3172719 basin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  out and get so much for a ha'penny you know and that - made quite a lot of herb beer. We used to go round the fields getting herbs you know then. You could make nettle beer and all you know and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What games did you play in the street, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well we used to have ropes and play at skipping. 'Course that road at Hilltop then, you know, that new pub, that's where I was born.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 The Man in Space?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 In Space. Well that road wasn't very wide then. We used to h
ave circuses come through here, elephants and they were - all walked, yes. We often - where I lived we often pulled a cabbage out and threw it on the road for them. 'Course we'd all gates - we kept all the gates shut you know while they were going through
 Such things as that, that were your life then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were you allowed to get dirty when you were playing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, used to get dirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you feel that you could play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, we could - mind you there was some ruffians
 in Hilltop in those days, of course we used to - sort of keep together, you know, all certain parts if you understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh they wouldn't - if they knew you were playing with certain - my word - certain lads you know you would get - something for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, there weren't many then you know, not really. There was just the - churches and chapels, that sort of - then see - well - was
 the Boy's Brigade, they were the first lot to come out I think. Then the Scouts I believe, I believe the Boys Brigade was the first. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How did you spend your free time apart from what you've told me about playing and that, can you remember any oth
er ways you spent your free time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't think so. No. We used to collect horse manure off the roads you know in a bucket for the garden. Yes. They used to do that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You helped in the garden did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, I have - I always have liked a garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you keep any pets as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Oh used to have cats. Mother, she was very fond of a cat. I don't remember us having a dog, no. No. But they bought a dog down from Bedfordshire with them, I've heard them say. Of course I can't remember that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
No. We used to go paddling. You know, the brook's over here in the hollow. And we used to call it brook bottoms. And we used to - perhaps have two or three slices of br
ead wrapped up in newspaper and a bottle of water. That's how we used to go - summertime. 'Cos there were no money to buy sweets. Mind you if I did a get a ha'penny I could get two ounce of lovely sweets then for a ha'penny, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Who would you go up to the brook with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well - there'd be six or seven of us. Perhaps more. Children from the district yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you ever do any cycling as a lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 I did have one, then you see this happened, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 When you were a schoolboy did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well we used to have games you know, ordinary games in the - playground.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You were telling me pantomimes and that sort of thing weren't encouraged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh no, we never went to things like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you ever go to a music hall or a concert or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
No. No. Only if there were local concerts at the chapels. Used to get - the sketches you know and sing you know. Of course some good singers about in those days. Yes. Mind there was more - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10186699\charrsid3172719 
home life}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  then, you see, people had got an instrument and friends used to go you know and - and have tea parties on Saturdays at the chapels and - you'd perhaps pay ninepence. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 You'd get a ham and tongue tea then for ninepence and sixpence for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3172719  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 children. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Then there'd be a concert afterwards you see. You see, we never went in - there were nowhere to go, you'd no idea of going anywhere, you were content then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you get pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Pocket money? Oh I didn't get much. About - about tuppence a week perhaps. And I was better off 
than a lot you know. 'Cos they hadn't got money to live let alone pocket money. And we used to have a good Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What did you spend yours on, just sweets was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Just sweets, yes. And monkey nuts and bananas. Yes. Things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. Only the - help as we had you know, I told you about her didn't I. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 But not relations or friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No, I don't remember, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well - we'd this help in the same as I say, you see. Yes. Yes. You see, there was four of us then. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 Granddad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  and dad and mother and myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 When your younger brothers were born, what happened then, who would run the house? Your mother would be confined to bed wouldn't she?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, well we did have - a neighbour in. Don was born up here, yes. We had all friend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 s of that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  sort of - you know. We didn't have nurses when Don was born. Well they were very - few an
d far between. We had an old lady but - and she saw the job through - of course the doctor came as well. Yes. Of course - confinements then, they seemed to get on all right. Quicker than they do today. In my opinion. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were there any other relatives of your parents living nearby apart from your grandfather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
There was dad's mother. Grandmother Soar. She was cousin to Mrs Pankhurst. Yes. The Mrs Pankhurst. Mind we don't think much about it but she was. Of course I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You can't remember whether she was active in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. What, Grandma Soar, oh no. No, she kept herself - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You saw these relations quite frequently then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes. Grandfather - Bygrave that was. I didn't know Grandfather Soar. He died before I was bo
rn. And Grandma Bygrave was you see. Yes. Yes, she died in 1888. Grandma Bygrave. 'Cos I tell you, they used to - in those days you know they used to have memorials. Used to make black wool on sort of canvas and they had them }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 framed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  and hung up, well there
 was one in my bedroom. I've read it a million times. I can tell you what it said. It said, in loving memory of Eliza Jane Bygrave. Died February 13th 1888 aged }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 forty-nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  years. And they used to frame it and hang it on the wall. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your parents have any friends in the locality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Oh - a lot of friends. All church people you see they were - more people of course in that day went to church and chapel than they do today, because they were - there were no more amusements if you understand. Wasn'
t nothing ; that was your life. Part of your life you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 So the friends were mainly connected with the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 And they would see them at church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 That's right, yes. And - and - well, they'd visit us and we used to visit them o
ccasionally you see. It was - as I say, that was your life then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You were telling me your mother had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  great interest in the organ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did she have any friends of her own, that were not shared with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't think so. No, oh no, we were always one you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your father have any special friends of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, no, just about ordinarily. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Friends would be invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. And then you'd go and visit them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 About how often do you think you would exchange visits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Well now then we'd some friends in - you know the Hardstaff Homes at Gitl Road, yes, well we'd some friends there. And used to go to church and then we'd walk down there with them. And then walk ba
ck to Hilltop, well that was your Sunday evening, if you understand. Of course dad didn't go with us. There was only mother and myself then 'cos Don wasn't born you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 When your friends came into the house was it normal for them to be invited to have something to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Oh yes, if they came they'd have - cup of tea or - whatever was going you see. Not - often for meals if you understand. No, just a sort of friendly gesture.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were there any particular days or occasions when friends came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No. We'd either have relatives -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Generally speaking they would be friends of both your mother and your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. That's right, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was it normal for people to pop in without invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, not very often. No, without - there was some business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did neighbours pop in without invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. Not very often. No, we didn't - 'cos we saw them on the yard you know. It was one long yard if you understand, six houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Your parents mainly went out for church activities then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. That was about all. Of course, dad, he'd go for a bit of cricket sometimes you know. Just local, not - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 We're often told that in those days people made their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What did your parents do when they got together with their friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh just sort of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Music - have a musical evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Sometimes, just a little bit and - gossip of course and - events of the day, then you know, what was going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did they play any games, like some people played cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, no, never did anything like that. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, I've always thought that really. I mean there were chaps that
 - wouldn't work you know, and spend most of their time in the pubs drinking and their families and wives starved to death. Of course - you know in that day everybody knew everybody. In a place like this. We knew everybody and they knew us. You see, there
 
weren't many houses in Hilltop then. There were nothing down here, nothing there, nothing - all fields behind here where you are you know. No council houses. And these houses - well, Nottingham Road it'd come down to Bridges College about you know, that's
 - that's all. Where that is - there was an old cottage, I remember it. Oh yes, well Eastwood wasn't built - no church new estate there, nothing like that. I've told you before, you could stand on Hilltop and see Crouch Stand. Quite easily.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 But where Lawrence was born in Victoria Street there and Argyll Street, those were old miners' cottages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Yes. Oh yes, they've been there. Oh a hundred years - hundred and fifty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Because that's the old part of Eastwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, that's the old
 part. That was a quarry you know years ago. Yes, that was a quarry. 'Cos you see, that Congregational church, that's coming down isn't it. Well it's - closing anyway. Well that was a quarry there. Yes. That was my first school there in 1901. British scho
o
l we called it then at Eastwood. Of course you could go where you liked then you know. And I went there about six years, then I went to Beau Vale you see. In that time - Lawrence had been there and he'd sort of gone again. But I knew him you know. I knew 
who he was if you understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You knew him as a lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Yes, that's right. Well he'd be older than me you know. Oh yes, yes, yes. He'd be a young man when I was a boy. Oh how old would be - I should think he'd be ten years older than me perhaps. How
 old would he be now? 'Cos I can remember him as a big tall lanky chap. When I remember him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You remember}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719  s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 eeing him about do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, he used to be about, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What was he doing when he was a young man when you knew him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well I -
 I didn't know as he did anything, he was always sort of - you know, dressed up and walking about if you understand. I never knew him - of course I can't remember that, no, of course he wasn't thought of then as he is now. No. No. I knew his cousins, a lo
t of his cousins - round about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 He ran away with that professor's wife didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I can't - no, you see, I shouldn't be - at that age then for - if you understand. No. And you know we weren't forward
 like they are today. I didn't - I was fourteen before I knew where a baby came from.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Looking back on the community before the first world war if you were asked to look back and say the community was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 divided}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  into certain social classes, how would you roughly define each group? You had your mining group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Of course a lot of miners they went to chapel in those days. Yes. Now that Congregational church, we used to call that Butty's Lump. Now do you know what a butty is in a pit? Well he's a man that
 had so much - coal length if you understand to work. Yes. Yes. And they knew the good men you know, the - managers and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 So the chapel was called that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, that was it - the Congregational. Used to call it Butty's Lump. Yes. And the gaff
ers used to go there and they'd expect these men to go, if they give 'em a good place to work in, you see. They had to go whether they wanted or not. Oh that was - that was everywhere, it was at Greasley church. And Major Barber was there, I know it was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 From the colliery which is now Moor Vale?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Yes. Well they'd all those collieries, he lived at Lamb Close you know. You know that don't you. Lamb - you know Lamb Close. Do you know the reservoir? Well it's past there just on that side as you go rou
nd, Lamb Close stands there. Well his son's there now in't he. Those - those two sons, one got killed I think in - was it a - oh the '42 war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Butty means a strip of coal you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. The butty's the man. Yes. Well he'd have a certain strip of co
al to get and make the best out of it you see and - it'd be a good job for him. Yes. Now you see these houses up here, the first lot as I've told you about, they were all built from the pay miners. They'd got good jobs, can you see, til you got down to th
e hairdresser's, you know that don't you. All those were individual houses and most of them were built with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 butties}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
. Yes. So of course, I told you before, they never put baths in them then, they weren't - up to date as that, as they are now. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was there any sort of feeling of a working class group and upper classes and that sort of feeling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Oh yes, there was that - there was always that feeling, I mean - some of these gaffers - they call them gaffers you know, the pit - well they - they'd ha
ve a pony and trap to ride in you see and - you wouldn't meet them walking if you understand. You knew where they lived of course and - but that was as much as you saw of them, you see. Then there were lower class of course as - wouldn't work, never did w
ork and never would and - they were sort of - you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 So you had the three distinct groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Yes. Yes, that's right, that's how it was in those times. 'Cos I can remember mother saying to, me, old so and so is going in that pub again and - I can remember that. You see, they'd spend all their money in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What sort of group would you put you and your family in, the ordinary working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 In this area then in that group you'd have miners then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Would there be anybody else belonging to that group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh - no, wouldn't be many 'cos it was mostly miners here when I was young you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Further out towards Langley Mill and Heanor you got the lace trade didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Of course you did, yes. Fletchers, that's right. Of course Vic }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 Allen
\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  wasn't thought of then you know. No. Then there was Smith's mill you know, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 who}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  owned the mill. That's been there - that was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 What did this mill produce?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well they used to grind 
corn - flour. Flour mill, yes. Yes. And then there was Turners you know. Iron foundry wasn't it, then there was the pottery you know, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 Lovatt's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 . Oh yes, pottery in them times. Oh yes. And it went all over the world their stuff did. Some people they'd like to get hold of some. Langley mill there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 It had a name did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. For the Hilltop girls you know, they used to call them pottery maids. Yes, there was always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 Lovatt\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 So you've actually got pottery with the Langley Mill stamp on it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Yes. So that's it - that there. Now I can remember girls walking from Kimberley, you know where Kimberley is, to Langley Mill and then they'd walk back. The pottery at Langley Mill, yes. And - when I was a boy. 'Cos - I used to - we used to see them g
oing backwards and forwards.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 It isn't there now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How long do you think it's been closed - down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh it's not that many years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 But it was a thriving industry when you were a lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh it was, yes, thriving industry then, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Who would belong to the upper classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Well you'd say the managers at the pits for a start and - shop proprietors in Eastwood and - you understand. No, I don't think they would be. Of course - local tradesmen, you know what I mean, those that - that owned their own business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No, I don't remember that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were you ever taught to touch your cap to anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes. Oh we had to do that when we were younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Who would that be to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well - the schoolteachers you know and people like that. If you went to church and met anyone you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 This was as a mark of respect was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, that's right, yes, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Who would you call sir in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Well - these poorer class'd call a lot of people sir you know, so it - as if they were, you know - bending to them if you understand. Toadying - that's what we used to call it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Do you remember anyone showing respect in any particular way to your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No I don't know, not particularly. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 In the district then who were generally considered to be the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well - Mr Barber, he wasn't liked a lot then you kn
ow, not Major Barber. He was important but he wasn't liked a lot, because they were all Liberals you know and Labour. That day. And they weren't - of course there were the Conservatives and - they kept together you know. They were a strong band, a strong 
- yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 But he would be regarded as important because he was a big employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Yes, he was a big employer but people didn't see him very often. You see, they - they went away a lot didn't they in those days. People that had got the money went to Swi
tzerland and places like that you know. Buxton - and places like - they went there then you know for the waters and - things like that, yes, and Bath you know. Well they did didn't they. And Matlock and that, yes. Well that's nothing today you see, things
 have altered and - well people can go anywhere you see, I'm a poor man aren't I. Well you see what I mean, you see, I couldn't get to Switzerland now. I'm not penniless but you know what I mean. Of course we're not in that class. Barber - Major Barber.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were any others regarded as important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well - not exactly here, there was at Langley Mill. Smith you know. The millers and then there'd be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 Lovatt\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 , they were the - I'm just thinking about that pottery. The proprietors they were - Reg Lovatt
, I think they lived a high life and - lost interest in the business you know. You know how it was a made in those days, the young parents they had to work didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What about shopkeepers, who did they associate with, more or less among themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, well and with us I mean - it was different then you know. You could go in any shop and have a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 gossip.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  That was the life because there would be nowhere to go, there was no money to go anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What about the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 clergy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  and teachers and people like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Oh they were different then. They'd visit. If you - didn't go they'd soon be coming to the house to see what was the matter. Well I - go up onto Greasley and Eastwood all me life, I don't think any minister's been here. Not to see me as f
ar - well, one came when I lost me brother. But I wasn't at home, I'd gone out on business. That were Mr - whatsishame at Eastwood - Derek - oh, what's Rector's name, in't it funny -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 The one now you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes - Derek - yes, he's on council. Good
man that's it. Yes, I can remember things and - when you're getting older you know names seem to leave you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Did you ever get the impression that the clergy and the teachers and the employers were sort of associating with each other, or didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Well they did to a certain extent, not - I don't think they'd be ever so friendly if you understand, they'd just - because they sort of had to, do you - didn't they. You see, there were different things cropped up and they're - all interested in you k
now and they'd have to get together wouldn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What sort of people would you say went to church as distinct from chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh well - the same class but they were poor people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Who went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, and church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 They'd be both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Yes. Now each Christmas, when - Major Barber he's died of course - and his mother was alive at Lamb Close, every Christmas they - they'd let people, you know, poor people that they'd something for them if they'd go up to Lamb Close. Well they used t
o go at a certain time and they'd give them blankets and sheets and clothes you see. Mrs Baber'd give them these because - of course she'd get a list from the church and you see that made people go just the same as I've told you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Or would you say there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. All about the same, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You were telling me about some of the families who lived at a rather low level?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you get the feeling that the ordinary working class people felt themselves a bit superior to this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 other group}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well they would do - the lower group altogether, yes. Of course, the - the working man, they weren't much better off then yo
u know. Of course you've got this respectability born in you if you understand. And you'd keep it if you was poorer. And you - you see what I mean? Yes, you'd keep that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 But some families were thought of as rough weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes. Rough, ye
s, they'd do anything. Wouldn't care - it was how they were brought up you see. Now we used to have - lantern processions when I was a boy at church. And - perhaps say October when it was just getting dark and we used to have long canes and a lantern fixe
d
 on with a candle in. Well these all used to be lit and we used to parade the streets. We had a band and - collected money for the church. Well there was - you know, there were stones on the road, them big tank stones. They weren't tarred like they are no
w you know, you could just - well one youth threw at these lantern and it hit me dad here and knocked him out. Yes, sent him unconscious, I remember that ever so well. Out of devilment you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 That was a youth from one of these .....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, down Cavendish Street, I remember it ever so well. I wasn't very old, I must be seven or eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well I think they did, yes. My }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 granddad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  Bygrave, he was a Conservative you know. Of course I didn't hear them talk much about politics. Not in that day, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 I think she did a little bit. I've heard people say - Grandmother Bygrave, she was a ve
ry refined women. Of course I - I didn't know her. Of course I didn't, she died in 1880 and I never heard them say much about her. No. Of course I used to go to church with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 Granddad}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  Bygrave, Sunday mornings you know, Greasley. We'd a - a Pole, Baron von Hube, he was the vicar then at Greasley. Baron von Hube. Yes. Yes. Yes, that's right. Baron von Hube. Von Hube. Yes, the 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 Baron}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
 and the Baroness. Well the Baroness used to come to our house sometimes, walk from Greasley to Hilltop. And we'd a little organ, Am
erican organ, and she always used to go in the front room and play this. Oh yes, there was a Baron and Baroness. I can see them now. Von Hube. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 Separately}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  you know. Yes, von Hube.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 And they were Greasley Parish church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, he was the Vicar. Vicar
 is at Greasley. Rector is at Eastwood in't it. Yes. Oh yes, I remember them, they'd no family. No. They lived in that big place. 'Course it's not the vicarage now is it. Greasley. Well you know where the vicarage is on the hillside don't you at Greasley.
 
I don't know, I believe it belongs to the old man doesn't it, Mr Nolan, I believe it does. they bought it. Their farm's next to the church, Greasley Castle. They - you've seen that ruin there haven't you. If you - look closely you'll see part of the Greas
ley old castle. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 In the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
No, on the farm. Next to a byre you'-l see a corner. And that's part - the remains of Greasly Castle, and the moat's still there I think. Yes. It is. That's next to the church. Yes, that's right. You can see i
t quite plain from the road. And if you go up the drive you can see the moat. Now further down there's an old - very old building you know. Bog End - Bog End they call it. That was where my dad went to school, the old schoolhouse was there. They paid four
pence a week then. It's there now. Only you know they made that new road up to the bottom of the hill didn't they. Well that part's cut off, well it isn't cut off but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Church road isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, you don't use it very much now. Well Bog End, you'
ve seen that very old cottage there. Yes. Well that's the old school. Yes. That's a some years ago, our father was there and he'd have been a hundred. Yes. Yes, he'd have been about a hundred now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was it possible then to move from one class to another, can you remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 
anyone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't think so. No. You'd keep - you'd keep it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You pretty well kept to your own groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Do you ever remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Well I have heard it mentioned, like if they'd done anything good, if there'd been a strike and - they'd perhaps - lend you a few bob, five }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 shillings.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  As - as little amount as that, well it'd save some people you know from being starved to death.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 It would be a term to describe the way a person helped somebody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Yes. Oh yes, other people that - they weren't in the miners union. And it was - oh it was sixpence a week then I think it was. They wouldn't put in, well they hadn't the money perhap
s and then you see they were destitute. Used to have soup kitchens you know, anything -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 It wasn't necessarily a phrase that meant somebody who was rich?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Someone who was helpful to their fellow man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Fellow man, that's righ
t. Of course if you gave sixpence away then it was a lot of money. It was, oh my word. Though I don't remember much being given away myself, not - not generally if you understand. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes. Saw them all come down here two or three times a day. There was no cars then you know, it was - all walking in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Do you remember what you thought of the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh we were always frightened to death of the policeman. I mea
n if you did anything wrong they scuffed you, they wouldn't today you know would they, they daren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How do you think he treated people generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Policeman? Oh they were all right if you were. And they were more - you know, more free than they are today. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 So you think the policeman treated people fairly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were the houses you lived in rented houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you ever see anything on the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. He had a collector. Of course - tha
t one down here belonged to me auntie you know. Yes, me mother's sister. See, yes, that's right, we came down there to live by them when Uncle Jim built those two houses. Where Mr Bygrave is now you know, the older. Of course they didn't have any - well t
hey'd a daughter, they hadn't any sons. So - Jack got the business. He}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719  was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  a brother you see. There was four }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 ygraves, two daughters and two sons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you have any feelings about the landlord?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I remember the collector, she came from Moor Gre
en, a Mrs - what was her name - Stubbs. I really couldn't say who the houses belonged to there up Hilltop. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. Not my parents, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What difference did it make to the family if your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well he wasn't out of work, I don't remember him ever being out of work, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Nor ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 So you never had to go to the Guardians or the Parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 If there w
as someone in the district who the people disapproved of very strongly for misbehaviour of any kind was there any special way in which the people showed their disapproval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well they would shun them, they wouldn't have to speak to them. If they met th
em or anything like that - but - I don't think anything else, got any further like in the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You don't remember rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, no, no. Of course if anything went wrong badly we'd get policeman you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were you ever given lessons by one of your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. A lot before I went to school, 'cos mother was a schoolteacher you see. Did me good if you understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 That was before you actually went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, before I actually went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Five. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 When you first started what time in the morning did you go?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 About half past eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What time did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 I said before I came back for midday dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Then you went back to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Yes, I went back to school. Be about quarter of an hour's walk. From Hilltop to Eastwood, 'cos of course we sauntered on the way a bit you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What time did you get back in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 About four. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 So when you started at five you did morning and afternoon school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 In some parts they did morning only didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 But you did all day from five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What kind of school was it, a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Church, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 It was a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was it mixed or boys only?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Mixed it was. Yes, boys and girls, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 And you walked to school and it took you about a quarter of an hour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Who would you normally go with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well I went - there
 was this teacher lived at Hilltop, a Miss Gail, I remember she was in lodgings and I used to go backwards and forwards with her when I first commenced. Of course as you get on you don't - bother with that if you understand. That was just for the break in
 if you understand. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You came home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well I didn't like it at first, it was too confined you know. When you've had liberty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 But generally after that did you get to like it more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, settled down, yes. Never thought anything about it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well they was all right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Can you ever remember them emphasising certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't remember. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 I was thinking of things like manners or punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Oh yes. Yes. No, I don't think so. Of course I were - I was - oh not swaggering off, but I was brought up a bit different. Some of them you know. When you're parents been a teacher they - they know what - what's what don't they. To a certain extent.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh used to get the cane then you know. Have to go into the front and hold your hand out and get a slash.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were the girls treated the same as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 For what sort of offences would you get the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well if you were taking and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 laughing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  you know and - giggling at one another, anything like that. Just misbehaving.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Your mother would take an interest in your schoolwork wouldn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes. Yes, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did she ask you about what you were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did she ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't remember, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Or meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I think they knew them personally but without meeting them you see. 'Cos they know who you are when you start and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did the other children at the school come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Yes. They were most of them }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 miners\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  children you know. A lot of them lived where Lawrence was born, all those houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Round Victoria Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. All came. The buildings they call that you know. It's still called the Buildings now. Yes. Still called the Buildings. And they use
d -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Why were they called the Buildings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
I don't know I'm sure. Mind you there were better class lived in them then when I was a boy than now you see. People come in from different places and you don't know what they are and - now a lot of that property, it's got to come down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 It's very rough round there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Yes, well - in - when I went to school it was a different again, it was like this, everybody took a pride in their house. Now it's - that's all gone. Those people have all moved to bet
ter surroundings. 'Cos the same as I say these 'ere rough people came in and - wanted places and they've ruined the place, that's the trouble. Of course there's no bathrooms when - but they weren't - bad cottages. No, I've been in - I've been in 'em all m
y
 life, different people you know. And warm kitchens too. That'd be the back door there as you might think. No porch, no other - out in the elements there, and you couldn't feel any draught, they fit that - you know, fit - oh perfect fit it was, the doors 
and the windows. Of course the wood was seasoned then, different from what it is today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did the teachers ever single children out for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No, I don't remember it, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Can you remember any gangs or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 troops}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well there used to - we probably used to have gangs in the playground you know. A certain lot'd stick together if you understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were any children ever left out of things at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you go on to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Beau Vale, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Until you were how old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You went right through?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You still came home to dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How long did it take you to get to school there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well about the same. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Was this school pretty well the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. About the same. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Can you remember why you left one school and went to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well - they thought it was a little nearer. You see I was down this hill then and I was 
on the top of the other hill. On the way to Eastwood. That's why I moved and went to Beau Vale.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You were fourteen when you left school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Do you think you would have stayed on longer if you'd have had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No I don't think so. You were ready to leave and have some - a change if you understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you ever do any part time education afterwards like evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, I had evening classes, yes. Yes. Especially when I got offered this job 'cos I know - my living'd be clerking then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No. I went to Heanor's Technical. We used to walk you know. Hilltop to Heanor. And walk back. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 While you were still at school did you ever have a part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well I was at Saxton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 s at Eastwood. They were grocers. Down Church Street. It belonged to Co-operative Society now that shop does. They've gone - they died off you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What was your job then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Just helping in the grocers shop. And it was a beer off too and you'd all the fixtures to fill up and empty bottles to - oh I worked harder then than - any time in my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How did you get the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well - my auntie got me the job next door, Mrs Witham. 'Cos they went to the Congregational church. And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 Saxton's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 , they give Uncle Jim Witham work, you see, that's how it is today in't it. You trade 
with them, they'll trade with you. Well they - they wanted a boy so I went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What sort of jobs did you do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well anything, want to weigh stuff up, flour and sugar and - clean currants in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12798422\charrsid3172719 sieves}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  you know and - do the fixtures and - oh it was a hard job. It was, for a starter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What hours did you work when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Oh - half past eight 'til half past eight at night. Saturday'd be half past eight 'til half past ten - Saturday night. And we used to have a half a day on Thursdays, w
ell - we couldn't - we didn't have half a day, 'cos it was two or three when you got finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You didn't work on Sunday though did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you have holidays with pay can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. Wasn't any holidays then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Can you remember what you were paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Four shillings a week. Four shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Can you remember if you felt anything about the wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No, I never thought whether it was fair, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 I give it to her all. I think I had about sixpence. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What would that three and six that you gave your mother be spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well - for keeping me I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Just the general sort of budget of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How did you get on with the other people that you worked with there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh - fair enough. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well - he was all right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh you had - you had to work then you know. There were no - slinking about and having cups of tea and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you like it or dislike it, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 I liked it all right as far as I remember. Well that's what it had got to be hadn't it. No students - the
re were no money then for students and allowances and - like they're better off now then when I went to work. They're not working at all. No. And then they think they're hard done to don't they. They want to have a packet. They do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did the job alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you ever think of your schooldays in a different way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't think so, no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You didn't do any part time jobs did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. Never had any part time jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How long did you do that job at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6565454\charrsid3172719 Saxton\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 About a year I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Where did you go to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Moor Green - colliery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What was your job there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well I - worked in the wood yards first. Supplying the - you know, they were the old fashioned saws then
. They were electric of course. Sawing wood up you know. I - I fed the men you see, carried the timber to them for the saws. Pit props and - all sorts of things. Then I went - I moved from there, I went on - bank then, on the pit bank. Bank. That's what t
hey call it at top you know, pit bank.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What did you do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well I used to help a man to oil the machinery. And that's how this got in you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 And you lost your arm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Can you tell me about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well, I tell you
 once, I got it in the belt in the machinery, I - I was about a year I think. We used to go to Nottingham - I forget - General Hospital, out patient and we used to have to go to Newthorpe station then you know. To get to Nottingham. Oh I got over it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 So you lost your arm when you were how old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Fifteen. Then I made fifty years after that. In the offices round about you know. I was on the pit top thirty or forty years, weighing tubs as they come out of the pit you know. Do you know what I mean? Wel
l little tubs, there'd be anything from eight hundredweight of coal in - in them to - to about - fifteen hundredweight, it will depends - the height down the pit where they were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10041468\charrsid3172719  loading}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  it. And I was weighman you know, there was a weighman and a check weig
hman. Check weighman for the men, you know that don't you? Well I was the weighman you see. They'd be coming along like this all day. For eight hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 And you had to check weigh each one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes, he - all put in there, and check weighman and weighm
an and the weights. Different stalls, you'd got the number at the top, from two up to - well - as many stalls as there were you see. And it'd all go down under that - number you see, what was on them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 What hours did you work in this sort of job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Eight hours a day. With a twenty minutes snap. And it you wanted to go to the toilet, well - you couldn't go. They wanted to take you off, left the pit standing. Then you soon got the sack if you acted like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You had to be there because it was continuous?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Seven 'til three, they were going all that time. Yes. I had about fifty bob a week for that. The check weighman used to get twice as much and you had all the work to do. It's true. I had to call every week after that man to see that he was 
satisfied. See? So - oh it is - I often wondered more than half to tell you the truth, the worry and anxiety. Then if you were wrong the gaffers'd be on to you, for letting too much weight go on the wrong side. Can you see? You'd all - always got that pul
l
 on you. You don't know whether it were true or not. Anyway I did job for a - between ten - twenty and forty years. And the pits closed down you know and - I had other work then 'til I was sixty five. Well one thing I'm - let's see - I worked forty-five y
ears and never had a short week so I did do well didn't I.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You worked eight hour shifts then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Yes, well you'd got to finish after. Pit made the hours, seven 'til three. Coal came in. Then you'd all your work to do after, you might get another ho
ur and a half - finishing. You'd got to put it on a slip, every stall, what the number of trams and the number of hundredweights like. Then you'd got to reckon all that up and then you'd got to keep a copy yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you work Saturdays as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
That all depends, we did in winter. And in the war time. We made full days. Yes. They pay us for all the 1914 war. Of course if we - we knocked off and they hadn't orders and we hadn't trucks - I used to go in the office and help them you see to make me
 time out. In the general office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were there any holidays with pay in that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. Mind you I got me weekly wage. I was on the staff if - what they like to call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 And you were paid about fifty bob a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 'Course it - changed as ti
mes went on you know. I believe I got about fifty-five when I got married. 1919. I could save a bit out of that - then. I used to have twenty Players a week, they were elevenpence ha'penny. Last me a week. Now I smoke twenty a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you feel that was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Well you had to have it whether it was or not. 'Course they did - the unions did get you - you got a penny a day put on it was marvellous. The banks, I think their top rate was three and six a day. And they were married men with families.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Before you got married did you give any of these wages to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Oh yes. Yes, I used to - we used to say, do you tip up, you know, when I was a lad. Do you tip up or do you pay board? Tip up meant give it all to your mother. An
d if you paid board well you - you just paid your board and then you - you got your clothes and everything and that was just for your food. You'd got to keep yourself then you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 But if you gave the lot of your mother it was called tip up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How did you get on with the people you worked with at the coalmine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh - oh all right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Would you know your employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, I knew them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You knew the actual owner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh yes, knew Major Barber.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
Well we didn't see him very often. No. Have to be something very important if he came to the pit. Of course there was five pits then you know, there was Watnell, High Park, Moor Green, Brinsley and Selsdon. And I've weighed at all thos
e pits. In me time, yes. So I must have done - something right I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you ever feel that you liked or disliked your job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well didn't think that because I knew there were nothing else for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Since the first world war you did the same sort of job didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't think so. No. I thought as I could do the job you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you have to have any training period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No, no training. Mind you I was 
timekeeping before I had the weighing job. Well I did all my work in the weighbox you see, there was plenty of room. Of course I got - a insight into the men you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 I joined miners union and - clerks union and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you take part in any of its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No. Wouldn't have done I don't think. No, it was just pay and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Oh they'd different interests - of course, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well in working conditions and wages too. Yes. They'd think that a man that earned three and six a day it was too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 There was a conflict of interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Well they - they didn't like the workers you know and the workers didn't like them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10041468\charrsid3172719 amongst}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  the workers themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't think so. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Were you aware of a difference of interest between trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
No, no. I know once - I'm putting you off perhaps. One of the miners daughter's when she left school went to be a servant, one of the houses you know. And - the - it was one of the manager's houses and this managers wife had a friend and she came a
nd she said, well - you know - they'd just put - old age pensioners, they were out for more money. They were getting ten bob a week, and this woman said - well, you know, they ought to manage on ten shillings a week, it's plenty for them. I know that was 
said 'cos I - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Would you say that full time work had changed your general attitude to life in any way at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You continued to live at home after you left school didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. I lived at home 'til I was married and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did the fact that you were going out to work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Your brothers came later on anyway didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you spend your Sunday in any different way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. No, still went to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 And Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes. Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. Not when - not when I was younger I didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You were married in 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You didn't take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Well not for that - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 You didn't have any particular views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
No. No. No. Well I don't think you do really when you're young, not as how as you're - sort of brought up to it young you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 When you were a schoolboy you were telling me how you spent your spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you spend your spare time in any different way when you started working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No. Don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you go out much in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No
t a lot. We used to play about in the streets you know, 'cos I tell you there was no traffic then. No. Very little. Wednesday nights you know they used to bring the beast}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10041468\charrsid3172719 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719  to the different butchers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10041468\charrsid3172719 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 
 shops from Nottingham, and they had to walk you know then
. They walked and that was beast night we used to call it. Yes. We always used to have the gates all shut. 'Cos you know, some of these beasts they were very - wild you know at times. Oh that was a red letter night for us, beast night. Wait for them comin
g
 up this hill. There'd be so many for George Lever's and so many for somebody else and a sheep or two for that place and a calf for that and - oh it was - and you know, the same as I say, they used to get in the gardens sometimes and - oh pandemonium let 
loose then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15731475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 Did you make any new friends about this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13449680 BS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2626886\charrsid3172719 No, don't think so.
